{"type":"message","id":"4c880991","parentId":"f110daec","timestamp":"2026-05-21T18:53:28.898Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-05-21 19:53 GMT+1] Sessions purged from 87 to 0. Gateway restarted clean. Main and\nTelegram session files are preserved — they'll reappear when you\nsend your next message.\n\nCRITICAL INVESTIGATION: Before re-enabling ANY cron jobs, audit\nwhat went wrong. We went from 22 to 87 sessions in hours. Some\ncron job was firing every few minutes, spawning a new session\neach time. That's what burned through our tokens.\n\n1. List ALL currently active cron jobs\n2. Check each one's frequency — something was running far too often\n3. Check the health check script — was it restarting something\n every few minutes?\n4. Check the dispatcher — was it spawning new sessions in a loop?\n5. Report which cron job(s) caused the explosion\n\nDo NOT re-enable any cron job until I approve the fixed schedule."}],"timestamp":1779389608891}}
