{"type":"message","id":"727d911e","parentId":"bb97ecc0","timestamp":"2026-05-21T18:55:50.243Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-05-21 19:55 GMT+1] Not all cron jobs have a description, is the below list accurate for the cron jobs that are meant to be there\n\nDaily Station Check\nACTIVE\n\n0 23 * * *\nRun the daily station check and send a Telegram sitrep. Do NOT use any AI model calls — just use shell commands and file operations. 1. **System Heal\nLast: 20 May at 23:00\nNext: 21 May at 23:00\nMission Control Health Check\nACTIVE\n\n*/15 * * * *\nLast: 21 May at 19:45\nNext: 21 May at 20:00\nTask Dispatcher\nACTIVE\n⚠ 1 ERROR\n\nYou are the Task Dispatcher. Your job is to pick up backlog tasks and spawn sub-agents to complete them. 1. Read `~/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.js\nLast: 21 May at 19:41\nNext: 21 May at 20:11\nSessions Cleanup\nACTIVE\n\n0 2 * * *\nNext: 22 May at 03:00\nSession Auto‑Expiry\nACTIVE\n\n0 4 * * *\nNext: 22 May at 05:00\nError Spike Watchdog\nACTIVE\n\n*/5 * * * *\nLast: 21 May at 19:50"}],"timestamp":1779389750237}}
