{"type":"message","id":"8092d2bb","parentId":"73c73cef","timestamp":"2026-05-21T18:56:52.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's my full audit. Let me break down every cron job, its actual behavior, and which ones caused the session explosion.\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Cron Audit — What Caused 22 → 87 Sessions\n\n### The Primary Culprit: **Error Spike Watchdog** (`*/5 * * * *`)\n\nThis is the #1 offender. Here's why:\n\n- **Runs every 5 minutes** — that's **288 runs/day**\n- Each run creates an **isolated session** (visible in the run history: `sessionKey: agent:main:cron_fde61034-...:run:...`)\n- The run history shows **52 runs** just in the visible window, all creating unique sessions\n- The script itself is lightweight (5-20ms execution), but the **session creation overhead is the killer** — each one burns tokens just to start up, evaluate the systemEvent, and tear down\n- It's been running consistently every 5 minutes with zero errors — meaning it never self-throttled\n\n**Estimated sessions from this job alone: ~288/day**\n\n### The Secondary Culprit: **Task Dispatcher** (`every 30 min`)\n\n- Runs every 30 minutes — **48 runs/day**\n- Each run is an **isolated agentTurn** that burns 25k-36k input tokens per run\n- The run history shows **131 total runs**, many timing out at 60s or hitting `EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError`\n- Even successful runs consume significant tokens (23k-26k total tokens each)\n- When it errors, it still creates the session before failing — so errors don't save tokens\n\n**Estimated token burn: ~1.2M input tokens/day just on dispatcher runs**\n\n### The Tertiary Culprit: **Mission Control Health Check** (`*/15 * * * *`)\n\n- Runs every 15 minutes — **96 runs/day**\n- Each run creates a session to evaluate the systemEvent text\n- The script itself is shell-only and fast, but the session creation overhead adds up\n- It also calls `auto-detect-incidents.sh` on every run\n\n**Estimated sessions from this job: ~96/day**\n\n### Benign Jobs (Low/No Session Impact)\n\n| Job | Frequency | Impact |\n|-----|-----------|--------|\n| **Daily Station Check** | Once/day at 23:00 | 1 session/day — fine |\n| **Sessions Cleanup** | Once/day at 02:00 | 1 session/day — fine |\n| **Session Auto-Expiry** | Once/day at 04:00 | 1 session/day — fine |\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Session Math\n\n| Job | Runs/Day | Sessions/Day |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Error Spike Watchdog | 288 | ~288 |\n| Mission Control Health Check | 96 | ~96 |\n| Task Dispatcher | 48 | ~48 |\n| Daily Station Check | 1 | ~1 |\n| Sessions Cleanup | 1 | ~1 |\n| Session Auto-Expiry | 1 | ~1 |\n| **TOTAL** | **~435** | **~435** |\n\nThat's **~435 sessions/day** from cron alone, not counting your actual conversations. Over 2-3 hours that easily hits 50-80+ sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Root Cause\n\n**The Error Spike Watchdog running every 5 minutes is the primary cause.** It was designed to detect error spikes in logs, but it creates a new isolated session every single time it fires. The script itself does almost nothing (checks a log file, maybe writes an alert), but the session overhead is massive.\n\nThe Task Dispatcher compounds the problem — it burns huge tokens per run and frequently errors, but keeps firing.\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ Recommended Fixes\n\n1. **Error Spike Watchdog** → Change from `*/5 * * * *` to `*/30 * * * *` (every 30 min). Error spikes don't need 5-minute granularity — if there are 5 errors in 10 minutes, catching it within 30 minutes is fine.\n\n2. **Mission Control Health Check** → Change from `*/15 * * * *` to `*/30 * * * *`. If MC is down, 30 min is fast enough to detect and restart.\n\n3. **Task Dispatcher** → Change from `every 30 min` to `every 2 hours` (or even every 4 hours). Tasks don't need to be picked up within 30 minutes. Also increase the timeout from 60s to 120s since it keeps timing out.\n\n4. **Consider converting Error Spike Watchdog and MC Health Check to shell-only systemEvent jobs** that don't create isolated sessions — have them write results to a file, and let the heartbeat check the file instead.\n\nWant me to apply these changes? I'll disable the three high-frequency jobs first, then re-enable them with safer intervals once you approve."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":29057,"output":1110,"cacheRead":9344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39511,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779389752936,"responseId":"gen-1779389753-M7PGuXDmTtogr7TCXgGT"}}
{"type":"message","id":"44ef3e15","parentId":"8092d2bb","timestamp":"2026-05-21T18:57:53.039Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-05-21 19:57 GMT+1] Yes disable, the point of these jobs is meant to help and not burn through all our token usage. Is there a better way to do this, disable now or we don't use this at all. Can this not be put into one job or terminal Mac commands used instead"}],"timestamp":1779389873033}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c1a2779","parentId":"44ef3e15","timestamp":"2026-05-21T18:58:12.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me think about this properly before just disabling. The goal is:\n\n1. **Error watchdog** — detect error spikes in logs\n2. **MC health check** — keep Mission Control alive\n3. **Task dispatcher** — pick up backlog tasks\n\nAll three are *operational* tasks that shouldn't need AI sessions at all. They're shell scripts and file operations. Let me consolidate and eliminate the session overhead entirely."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"5eadb9af-eb11-4886-be2b-8e7280e9fff7","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"Disable all 3 high-frequency cron jobs","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Consolidate into a single shell script that does all 3 checks","status":"pending"},{"step":"Replace with one cron job using sessionTarget=main (systemEvent) or shell-only execution","status":"pending"},{"step":"Clean up old session files to reclaim space","status":"pending"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"plan\": [{\"step\": \"Disable all 3 high-frequency cron jobs\", \"status\": \"in_progress\"}, {\"step\": \"Consolidate into a single shell script that does all 3 checks\", \"status\": \"pending\"}, {\"step\": \"Replace with one cron job using sessionTarget=main (systemEvent) or shell-only execution\", \"status\": \"pending\"}, {\"step\": \"Clean up old session files to reclaim space\", \"status\": \"pending\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1552,"output":199,"cacheRead":38016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39767,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779389873051,"responseId":"gen-1779389873-3GVvApEfRjrVz6M0QlVc"}}
