.\n\n4. **Backup Check**: Check if `/Volumes/OpenClaw-WD` or `/Volumes/Public` is mounted. Check if today's backup file exists. Log result.\n\n5. **Daily Summary**: Append a brief summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` with: date, system health snapshot, git commit status, tasks archived, backup status.\n\n6. **Telegram Sitrep**: Use `curl` to send a one-line daily sitrep to Telegram chat 7507878944 via the OpenClaw gateway message API. The sitrep should include: tasks active count, tasks awaiting review count, disk %, and overall status (nominal/fail). Format example:\n   `📡 DAILY SITREP — 2026-05-16 | 3 active · 1 awaiting review · 85% disk · ✅ ALL SYSTEMS NOMINAL`\n   \n   If disk > 90% or any critical issues found, use `⚠️` instead and note the issue.\n   \n   Use the OpenClaw gateway to send: `openclaw message send --channel telegram --to 7507878944 \"<sitrep text>\"` or use the gateway HTTP API at localhost:18789.\n\nKeep it fast. Use exec for all operations. Do not call any models.","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"last","to":"7507878944"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1779400800000,"lastRunAtMs":1779314400008,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":90984,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"consecutiveSkipped":0,"lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","lastDelivered":true},"updatedAtMs":1779314490992},{"id":"6f823429-453b-4db5-a5c9-51472f1693b3","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Sessions Cleanup","enabled":false,"createdAtMs":1779373498843,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 2 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"openclaw sessions cleanup"},"state":{},"updatedAtMs":1779390222444},{"id":"c52ff1a0-0936-48f9-8247-3711020824ca","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Session Auto‑Expiry","enabled":false,"createdAtMs":1779373821493,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 4 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/session-expiry.sh"},"state":{},"updatedAtMs":1779390222446}],"total":3,"offset":0,"limit":3,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null,"deliveryPreviews":{"dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d":{"label":"announce -> telegram:7507878944","detail":"resolved from last, session agent:main:telegram:direct:7507878944"},"6f823429-453b-4db5-a5c9-51472f1693b3":{"label":"not requested","detail":"not requested"},"c52ff1a0-0936-48f9-8247-3711020824ca":{"label":"not requested","detail":"not requested"}}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779390500600}}
{"type":"message","id":"71758304","parentId":"9f3305f7","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:08:40.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — the three destructive cron jobs are **deleted** (gone from the list entirely). Only 3 remain: Daily Station Check (enabled, nightly) and two disabled ones.\n\nThe 87-session list you saw — those were **stale entries in `sessions.json`**. The gateway had already purged them from active memory, but the JSON file still listed them. The `openclaw sessions list` command now shows only **2 sessions**, which is correct — your main session and one Telegram session.\n\nLet me confirm the LaunchAgent that replaced everything is running:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"be352fb7-3992-4046-96dd-00936083fc8d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"launchctl list | grep com.openclaw.maintenance; echo \"---\"; cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/logs/maintenance.log | tail -5"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"launchctl list | grep com.openclaw.maintenance; echo \\\"---\\\"; cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/logs/maintenance.log | tail -5\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1643,"output":170,"cacheRead":62848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64661,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779390500613,"responseId":"gen-1779390500-JIgolMsCeTuyPyX3R7ge"}}
{"type":"message","id":"529e64e2","parentId":"71758304","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:08:40.115Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"be352fb7-3992-4046-96dd-00936083fc8d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-\t0\tcom.openclaw.maintenance\n---\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [7/9] Safe backup: not today (day 4)\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [8/9] Session cleanup...\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [8/9] Session cleanup: expired 0 stale sessions\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [9/9] Storage migration: not today (day 21)\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] === Maintenance run complete ==="}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"-\t0\tcom.openclaw.maintenance\n---\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [7/9] Safe backup: not today (day 4)\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [8/9] Session cleanup...\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [8/9] Session cleanup: expired 0 stale sessions\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] [9/9] Storage migration: not today (day 21)\n[2026-05-21 20:03:55] === Maintenance run complete ===","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779390520114}}
{"type":"message","id":"efb48483","parentId":"529e64e2","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:08:59.312Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the honest answer:\n\n**Yes, it's fixed.** The 87 sessions you saw were dead/stale entries in `sessions.json` left over from before the purge — the old cron sessions that already ran and finished. They're not active sessions consuming tokens. The current active count is **2** (main + Telegram), which is exactly right.\n\nThe three cron jobs that caused the explosion are **deleted entirely** — not just disabled, removed from the system. The `every` and `cron` intervals that were firing every 5/15/30 minutes are gone.\n\n**Replaced with:** One LaunchAgent (`com.openclaw.maintenance`) running pure shell every 30 minutes. The `openclaw sessions list` only shows 2 sessions now. The LaunchAgent won't create any new cron sessions — it's a background macOS process, not an OpenClaw cron job.\n\nThe one remaining enabled cron job — **Daily Station Check** — runs once a day at 23:00 and that's it. One session per day for the Telegram sitrep.\n\n**Before:** ~435 cron sessions/day burning tokens. **After:** 1 cron session/day + 48 LaunchAgent runs (zero tokens)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":463,"output":265,"cacheRead":64384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779390520115,"responseId":"gen-1779390520-pUoBbMdSOjwhM9wC3NG1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"79ec941e","parentId":"efb48483","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:11:10.467Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-05-21 20:11 GMT+1] The disabled cron jobs just be deleted instead\n\nThe Incidents & Alerts page shows the last incident as May 16th.\nToday is May 21st. Five days of operational events have not been\nlogged. We need to fix this.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nPART 1: DIAGNOSE INCIDENTS\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. Is the auto-detect-incidents.sh script still running? Check:\n - Is it in the maintenance.sh flow?\n - When did it last execute?\n - Does maintenance.sh call auto-detect?\n\n2. Read the current incidents.json:\n - What's the last INC-ID?\n - What's the last timestamp?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nPART 2: BACKFILL INCIDENTS FROM MAY 17-21\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nLog these events as new incidents:\n\n1. Gateway update failure — missing modules after partial update\n to v2026.5.19 (May 21, 14:58)\n2. OpenClaw gateway crash loop — EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError\n across all sessions (May 21, 15:15-15:20)\n3. Session explosion — 22 to 87 sessions in hours due to cron jobs\n creating isolated sessions instead of shell-only checks (May 21)\n4. Rate limit exhaustion — free-models-per-min from multiple\n simultaneous sessions (May 21)\n5. WD MyCloud mount path changes — /Volumes/Public-1 vs\n /Volumes/Public (May 21)\n6. Any other operational events from the gateway logs between\n May 17-21\n\nFor each incident, include:\n- INC-ID (incrementing from last)\n- Severity (P1/P2/P3)\n- Owner (relevant agent)\n- Timestamp\n- Summary of what happened\n- Resolution/fix applied\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nPART 3: VERIFY AUTO-DETECTION IS ACTIVE\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. Confirm auto-detect-incidents.sh is called by maintenance.sh\n2. Test it manually — run the script and verify it creates an\n incident for any current issue\n3. Confirm new incidents will be created automatically going forward\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nPART 4: VERIFY QUICK ACTIONS\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nTest that each Quick Action button is wired to a working function.\nDo NOT just click — verify the underlying command executes correctly.\n\n1. DREAMING TOGGLE — Toggle on/off, verify /dreaming status changes\n2. SYSTEM HEALTH — Return real CPU, disk, memory data\n3. OPEN CONTROL UI — localhost:18789 loads via curl\n4. RESTART MISSION CONTROL — Dev server restarts and returns 200\n5. PAUSE QUEUE — Toggle queue state, verify it pauses\n6. REFRESH MODELS — Re-run freeride auto successfully\n7. RUN BACKUP — Trigger backup to /Volumes/Public/, check log\n8. CLEAR CACHE — Clear FreeRide and API caches, verify\n9. RESTART GATEWAY — Gateway PID changes, comes back healthy\n\nFor each: ✅ Working / ⚠️ Broken (explain) / 🔴 Missing (no function)\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nREPORT\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n- How many new incidents were backfilled\n- Whether auto-detection is now active\n- Status of each Quick Action button\n- Any buttons that need fixing"}],"timestamp":1779390670461}}
