{"type":"message","id":"c4d5bd62","parentId":"3f93f1a8","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:12:25.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto-detect ran but didn't create any new incidents. That means either: (a) there are no current active issues to detect, or (b) the script has a bug. Let me check the script logic — specifically what triggers exist and why nothing is firing for today's known issues:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"804343f3-8257-4ad4-962a-9d337c985f9c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":452,"output":92,"cacheRead":67072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67616,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779390736068,"responseId":"gen-1779390736-dNNekX8nnfGjJxyw9UXr"}}
{"type":"message","id":"11e79236","parentId":"c4d5bd62","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:12:25.613Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"804343f3-8257-4ad4-962a-9d337c985f9c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Auto-detect incidents from system state\n# Called by health-check-mc.sh every 15 minutes\n# Pure shell — zero model calls\n\nWORKSPACE=\"$HOME/.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE\"\n[ -z \"$WORKSPACE\" ] && WORKSPACE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace\"\nINCIDENTS_FILE=\"$WORKSPACE/data/incidents.json\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/logs/health-check-restart.log\"\nALERT_FILE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/mount-alert.txt\"\n\ntimestamp() { date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'; }\n\n# Helper: create incident via Python (since we need JSON manipulation)\ncreate_incident() {\n    local title=\"$1\" severity=\"$2\" owner=\"$3\" summary=\"$4\" tags=\"$5\" source=\"$6\"\n    python3 << PYEOF\nimport json, os\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\npath = \"$INCIDENTS_FILE\"\nincidents = json.load(open(path)) if os.path.exists(path) else []\n\n# Deduplicate\nfor i in incidents:\n    if i[\"status\"] != \"RESOLVED\" and i[\"title\"] == \"$title\" and \"$source\" in i.get(\"tags\", []):\n        print(\"duplicate\")\n        exit(0)\n\nnums = []\nfor i in incidents:\n    m = i[\"id\"].split(\"-\")\n    if len(m) == 2 and m[1].isdigit():\n        nums.append(int(m[1]))\nnext_id = f\"INC-{str(max(nums) + 1 if nums else 1).zfill(3)}\"\n\nnow = datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.000Z\")\ninc = {\n    \"id\": next_id, \"title\": \"$title\", \"severity\": \"$severity\",\n    \"status\": \"TRIAGE\", \"owner\": \"$owner\", \"acknowledged\": False,\n    \"escalated\": False, \"opened\": now, \"lastActivity\": now,\n    \"summary\": \"$summary\",\n    \"tags\": ${tags} + [\"$source\"],\n    \"timeline\": [{\"ts\": now, \"message\": \"Auto-detected by $source\", \"actor\": \"system\"}],\n    \"actions\": []\n}\nincidents.insert(0, inc)\nwith open(path, \"w\") as f:\n    json.dump(incidents, f, indent=2)\nprint(next_id)\nPYEOF\n}\n\necho \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] Running incident auto-detection...\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# ── 1. Check disk space ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nDISK_PCT=$(df / | tail -1 | awk '{print $5}' | tr -d '%')\nif [ \"$DISK_PCT\" -gt 85 ]; then\n    echo \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] Disk at ${DISK_PCT}% — creating incident\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    create_incident \\\n        \"Disk space critical — ${DISK_PCT}% used on root volume\" \\\n        \"P2\" \"lifesupport\" \\\n        \"Root volume disk usage at ${DISK_PCT}%. Threshold is 85%. System performance may degrade.\" \\\n        '[\"disk\", \"storage\", \"critical\"]' \\\n        \"disk-monitor\"\nfi\n\n# ── 2. Check WD MyCloud mount ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nif ! mount | grep -q \"/Volumes/Public\" && ! mount | grep -q \"/Volumes/OpenClaw-WD\"; then\n    # Check if we already have an open incident for this\n    if ! python3 -c \"\nimport json\nincidents = json.load(open('$INCIDENTS_FILE'))\nfor i in incidents:\n    if i['status'] != 'RESOLVED' and 'wd-mycloud' in i.get('tags', []) and 'mount' in i.get('tags', []):\n        exit(1)\nexit(0)\n\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        : # duplicate exists\n    else\n        echo \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] WD MyCloud mount missing — creating incident\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n        create_incident \\\n            \"WD MyCloud mount missing — backup storage unavailable\" \\\n            \"P2\" \"lifesupport\" \\\n            \"Neither /Volumes/Public nor /Volumes/OpenClaw-WD is mounted. Backup scripts cannot write to remote storage.\" \\\n            '[\"wd-mycloud\", \"mount\", \"backup\"]' \\\n            \"mount-monitor\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# ── 3. Check cron errors ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nCRON_ERROR_COUNT=$(python3 -c \"\nimport json, os\npath = '$WORKSPACE/data/cron-errors.json'\nif not os.path.exists(path): print(0)\nelse:\n    errors = json.load(open(path))\n    active = [e for e in errors if e.get('status') in ('new', 'in_progress')]\n    print(len(active))\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n\nif [ \"$CRON_ERROR_COUNT\" -gt 3 ]; then\n    echo \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] $CRON_ERROR_COUNT active cron errors — creating incident\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    create_incident \\\n        \"Cron job failures — $CRON_ERROR_COUNT active errors detected\" \\\n        \"P2\" \"lifesupport\" \\\n        \"cron-errors.json shows $CRON_ERROR_COUNT active error entries. Multiple cron jobs are failing.\" \\\n        '[\"cron\", \"failures\"]' \\\n        \"cron-monitor\"\nfi\n\n# ── 4. Check for stale tasks (>2h no activity) ──────────────────────────────\nSTALE_TASKS=$(python3 -c \"\nimport json, os\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\npath = '$WORKSPACE/data/tasks.json'\nif not os.path.exists(path): print(0)\nelse:\n    tasks = json.load(open(path))\n    stale = 0\n    for t in tasks:\n        if t.get('status') == 'in_progress':\n            stale += 1\n    print(stale)\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n\nif [ \"$STALE_TASKS\" -gt 2 ]; then\n    echo \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] $STALE_TASKS tasks stuck in progress — creating incident\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    create_incident \\\n        \"Tasks stuck In Progress — $STALE_TASKS tasks with no recent activity\" \\\n        \"P3\" \"monkey\" \\\n        \"$STALE_TASKS tasks are in In Progress state. Tasks without activity for extended periods should be reviewed.\" \\\n        '[\"tasks\", \"stale\", \"in-progress\"]' \\\n        \"task-monitor\"\nfi\n\n# ── 5. Check Mission Control health (dashboard down) ─────────────────────────\nMC_STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" --max-time 10 http://localhost:3000/)\nif [ \"$MC_STATUS\" != \"200\" ]; then\n    echo \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] Mission Control HTTP $MC_STATUS — creating incident\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    create_incident \\\n        \"Mission Control dashboard down — HTTP $MC_STATUS\" \\\n        \"P1\" \"engineer\" \\\n        \"Mission Control dashboard is not responding (HTTP $MC_STATUS). The dev server may have crashed or the port is occupied.\" \\\n        '[\"mission-control\", \"outage\", \"dashboard\"]' \\\n        \"health-check\"\nfi\n\necho \"$(timestamp) [AUTO-DETECT] Complete\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1779390745612}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e47c501","parentId":"11e79236","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:12:44.659Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue. The auto-detect script only catches **current active states** — it can't retroactively detect events that already happened. It checks: disk >85%, WD mount missing, cron errors >3, stale tasks >2, MC down. Right now all those conditions are healthy, so it correctly creates zero incidents.\n\nBut it's also **missing detection for**: gateway crashes, session explosions, rate limit exhaustion, update failures. These are transient events that the script never looks for.\n\nLet me now do Part 2 — backfill the missing incidents, then fix the auto-detect script to catch these event types going forward."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"9cd4cde0-bf08-41b6-a2dc-eed8311c6f42","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Find the highest INC number\nnums = []\nfor i in data:\n    m = i['id'].split('-')\n    if len(m) == 2 and m[1].isdigit():\n        nums.append(int(m[1]))\nprint(f'Highest INC number: {max(nums)}')\nprint(f'Next INC number: {max(nums) + 1}')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\n# Find the highest INC number\\nnums = []\\nfor i in data:\\n    m = i['id'].split('-')\\n    if len(m) == 2 and m[1].isdigit():\\n        nums.append(int(m[1]))\\nprint(f'Highest INC number: {max(nums)}')\\nprint(f'Next INC number: {max(nums) + 1}')\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1794,"output":262,"cacheRead":67456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69512,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779390745615,"responseId":"gen-1779390745-u39LdDdN0J37FZzW3W1K"}}
