{"type":"message","id":"505fea00","parentId":"6c4b90fc","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:18:00.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` is not set — it was a Python heredoc interpolation issue with the `$` signs. The `$WORKSPACE` var in the `create_incident` function was being expanded inside the Python heredoc. The fix is to use single quotes on the heredoc delimiter... wait, it already uses `PYEOF` (single-quoted). Let me check — the issue is that `$INCIDENTS_FILE` inside the Python heredoc gets shell-expanded because the heredoc var references use double-quoted strings that get interpolated. Actually no — `PYEOF` is single-quoted so nothing should expand. The error says `/Users/spacemonkey/.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` — note the uppercase. The env var `$OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` IS set somewhere... \n\nWait, looking again at the error: `'/Users/spacemonkey/.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE/data/incidents.json'` — that's the literal string `$HOME/.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` with `$HOME` expanded but `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` treated as literal text. That means in the Python section, the `$` in `$INCIDENTS_FILE` is being shell-expanded before Python sees it, and `$WORKSPACE` inside the Python code is being expanded too. Let me look at the actual content:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0f1d5a8a-c570-462e-a8e6-04141a5db218","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport os\nprint('OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE' in os.environ)\nprint(os.environ.get('OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE', 'NOT SET'))\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport os\\nprint('OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE' in os.environ)\\nprint(os.environ.get('OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE', 'NOT SET'))\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":337,"output":326,"cacheRead":77696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78359,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779391057396,"responseId":"gen-17793910