{"type":"message","id":"f44e1a18","parentId":"4b68d092","timestamp":"2026-05-22T00:43:37.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — the path is correct. The issue in the earlier test run was that the `create_incident` function's Python heredoc uses unquoted `PYEOF`, so shell variables like `\"$INCIDENTS_FILE\"` inside the Python code get expanded. But `$INCIDENTS_FILE` is set in the outer script scope, so it should work. Let me test the actual function call path:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2ab10ed3-d75c-431e-b380-1ead0ea2fa4c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Simulate what happens when create_incident is called\n# The issue: inside the Python heredoc, $INCIDENTS_FILE gets shell-expanded\n# But $title, $severity etc are function params — they also get expanded\n# The real question: does the expansion work correctly?\n\n# Test: run the script and check if incidents were created from the last run\ncat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(f'Total incidents: {len(data)}')\nfor i in data[:5]:\n    print(f'  {i[\\\"id\\\"]} | {i.get(\\\"opened\\\",\\\"?\\\")[:16]} | {i[\\\"title\\\"][:60]}')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Simulate what happens when create_incident is called\\n# The issue: inside the Python heredoc, $INCIDENTS_FILE gets shell-expanded\\n# But $title, $severity etc are function params — they also get expanded\\n# The real question: does the expansion work correctly?\\n\\n# Test: run the script and check if incidents were created from the last run\\ncat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nprint(f'Total incidents: {len(data)}')\\nfor i in data[:5]:\\n    print(f'  {i[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]} | {i.get(\\\\\\\"opened\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")[:16]} | {i[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"][:60]}')\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"o