{"type":"message","id":"06dc9935","parentId":"ceb4792f","timestamp":"2026-05-22T00:44:38.362Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is consistent — `.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` with a literal dot before it. That means `$HOME` is expanding to `/Users/spacemonkey/` and then `.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` is literal text. But that would only happen if the variable name is being split. Let me check — the issue is that in the Python heredoc, the shell is expanding `$INCIDENTS_FILE` which is `$WORKSPACE/data/incidents.json`. But `$WORKSPACE` is being set to `$HOME/.openclaw/workspace` — and the `$OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` env var is NOT set. So when the shell expands `$WORKSPACE`, it becomes `/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace`. Then `$INCIDENTS_FILE` becomes `/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json`.\n\nWait — the error says `.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` not `.openclaw/workspace`. The uppercase is the clue. Let me check if there's a `$OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE` being expanded somewhere:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6c81798a-6fb0-4e4e-bf66-e95946077a87","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check: is OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE set in the environment when the script runs?\nenv | grep -i workspace; echo \"---\"\n# Also check if the script itself has a typo\ngrep -n \"OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE\" /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check: is OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE set in the environment when the script runs?\\nenv | grep -i workspace; echo \\\"---\\\"\\n# Also check if the script itself has a typo\\ngrep -n \\\"OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE\\\" /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":498,"output":309,"cacheRead":54656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779410659285,"response