{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\n\nAdditional context from HEARTBEAT.md:\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- If a task is already `in_progress` and was started >2 hours ago with no progress update, reset it to backlog\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\nCurrent time: Friday, May 22nd, 2026 - 2:12 AM (Europe/London)\nReference UTC: 2026-05-22 01:12 UTC","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"1761ce45","parentId":"4fb799dc","timestamp":"2026-05-22T01:12:24.694Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"42c8761a","parentId":"1761ce45","timestamp":"2026-05-22T01:13:33.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me check for backlog tasks and handle the stale auto-detect incidents from the previous session."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"61639151-2d9e-4f3a-8333-93b236f360f6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ntasks = json.load(sys.stdin)\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'in_progress']\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In Progress: {len(in_progress)}')\nfor t in backlog:\n    print(f'  {t[\\\"id\\\"]}: {t[\\\"title\\\"]} (assignee: {t.get(\\\"assignee\\\",\\\"?\\\")})')\nfor t in in_progress:\n    print(f'  {t[\\\"id\\\"]}: {t[\\\"title\\\"]} [IN PROGRESS]')\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No tasks.json\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\ntasks = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'in_progress']\\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In Progress: {len(in_progress)}')\\nfor t in backlog:\\n    print(f'  {t[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]}: {t[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"]} (assignee: {t.get(\\\\\\\"assignee\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")})')\\nfor t in in_progress:\\n    print(f'  {t[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]}: {t[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"]} [IN PROGRESS]')\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No tasks.json\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":58253,"output":204,"cacheRead":640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59097,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779412344694,"responseId":"gen-1779412345-fNdIw8dasVfk0KfYaGrr"}}
